messages.message:
Team,
I am planning to clean up old code that supported loading messages from Amazon SQS to trigger flows. The code is broken and was based on old model of assuming space owner and user is same. I understand this was specifically developed for ~OpenLane~ LendingClub and not being used anymore. Tagging folks here who might have most context on this @shaunak @Ashish - please let know any concerns before we cleanup this code. Thanks!
Lending club instead of openlane. No customer is using it. Thank you for cleaning up

I’m not aware of this change.  I remember the ones where we configured SQS to send out notifcations after the flow had completed.  This was done for Lending Club who are not our customers.  @Ashish has the most context on this though.
Sorry my bad - thanks for correcting @Ashish
oh, my bad too — remember it the other way around :stuck_out_tongue:
